cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object tracking using convolutional neural networks.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a recurrent neural optimizer to update the tracking model in a meta-learning setting.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing an intelligent system for object tracking.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with tracking objects in real-time, which could have applications in robotics.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper deals with tracking objects in videos, which is a multimedia application.
